{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c946c0cd-09a8-4663-b393-96fd6462e77b","content":"On macOS, the OS automatically captures crash reports — no extra tooling needed.\n\n**Check these locations:**\n\n```bash\n# User crash reports (most common)\nls ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/*.ips\n\n# System-wide crash reports\nls /Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/*.ips\n```\n\nReports are `.ips` files (JSON format) named after your process. You can also open **Console.app → Crash Reports** to browse them.\n\n**For a core dump** (if you need one for lldb), enable them before reproducing:\n\n```bash\nulimit -c unlimited\n./your-app        # reproduce crash\nls /cores/        # core files land here\n```\n\n**Next step:** Once you have the `.ips` file, I can help you symbolicate the .NET runtime frames — just invoke the `apple-crash-symbolication` skill.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"30175277-2620-4433-8b0d-9fb1e3a7b782","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT app crash on macOS, specifically without createdump. This is a knowledge question about Apple's built-in crash reporting. Let me check if the apple-crash-symbolication skill or dump-collect skill would be relevant here.\n\nThe user isn't asking to symbolicate a crash log (apple-crash-symbolication) or to configure dump collection (dump-collect). They're asking where to find the crash report after a crash already happened. This is a straightforward knowledge question.\n\nOn macOS, when an app crashes, the system automatically generates crash reports (.ips files) in specific locations:\n\n\n- User-launched apps store them in ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n- System-level processes use /Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n- Console.app also provides a way to browse these reports\n\nSince createdump isn't available for NativeAOT on macOS, the system's native crash reporting mechanism is the way to go, generating .ips or .crash files automatically.","outputTokens":485,"requestId":"2C60:152429:2956E22:2DD6215:69F94C7F"},"id":"11ba8ebe-3173-42e1-b32e-acd8181b0df9","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:48:59.640Z","parentId":"ffacbe79-9e33-4589-b10b-7302c0b5e373"}
